SIMPLE: pugging
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pugging
<hw>Pug"ging</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Pug</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of working
and tempering clay to make it plastic and of uniform consistency, as for
bricks, for pottery, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Mortar or the like, laid between
the joists under the boards of a floor, or within a partition, to deaden
sound; -- in the United States usually called
<altname>deafening</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pugging</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pugging
<hw>Pug"ging</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Thieving.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

